e he struggles to earn a living and dreams of one day returning to his home.This graphic novel is necessary reading for our time. Alternately hopeful and heartbreaking, Hakim’s Odyssey is a story about what it means to be human in a world that sometimes fails to be humane.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aForced migrationzSyriavComic books, strips, etc. 0aRefugeeszSyriavComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / Biography & Memoir.2bisacsh1 aChute, Hannah.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074510840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978163779014440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781637790144423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781637790144/original  a978-3-11-074510-8  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK